Unlike cnf-from-ast, the SQL backends do not *reject* this example: the
Tseitin encoding has no non-linear recursion, so it translates to valid SQL
(see `--dry-run`). It is marked native-only because the shared truth-table
enumeration is impractically slow on SQLite once the variable count is
computed rather than a literal: SQLite regenerates the unmaterialized
assignment view inside the engine's correlated subqueries. The examples test
therefore skips the sqlite backend here and uses seminaive as the canonical
source for expected.json.
